{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow schools to teach BSL instead of a modern foreign language",
        "additional_details": "As the Government recognises BSL as an official language, it should have an equal place within the curriculum.\r\n \r\nWe believe this would be a move towards better inclusivity!\r\n \r\nCurrently if a school wishes to teach BSL this has to be in addition to MFL. With significant time pressure on schools, this is difficult to do.\r\n \r\nThousands of children in our mainstream schools rely on or regularly use BSL to support their education and/or communication at home.\r\n \r\nThis change would better allow schools teach BSL with the time and resources it deserves, and could help create an inclusive community and start children on a pathway to employment.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to change the criteria for teaching languages to allow primary schools to teach British Sign Language instead of a modern foreign language.",
